window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Impending, inevitable heartbreak never felt so good...</b></p> <p>The first time I met Damien Baxter, I told him to go eff himself. The second time I met him, I almost slapped him across the face after he made me cry. Third time’s a charm right? Wrong.</p> <p>But I have no choice. I’m stuck shadowing him at his company for the next two months. And if I want to achieve my dream of getting into the Ph.D. program I've worked toward my whole life, then I’m going to have to suck him up.</p> <p>It. Suck<i> it </i>up.</p> <p>If he has his way, though, the only<i> </i>thing I’m going to be learning from him is how to have my body utterly and completely ravaged and my heart broken. It sounds like a disaster just waiting to happen.</p> <p>So then, why can't I say no?</p> <p><i>Luxe</i> is the first book in Daisy Allen's hot new billionaire romance series, The Baxter Billionaires. It is a spicy, contemporary romance, interconnected stand-alone with no cheating and a HEA.</p>"; 
